CONNECTING TO A REMOTE MACHINE GUIDE
A. HOW TO CONNECT THROUGH RDP CLIENT (AWS/EC2)
1.	Select Connect on your instance dashboard.
2.	Select the RDP Client tab.
3.	Download the Remote Desktop File to your computer.
4.	Select Get Password.
5.	Upload your Private Key File (.pem) and click Decrypt Password.
6.	Copy the decrypted password to your clipboard and close the window.
B. HOW TO LOG IN TO THE MACHINE
Option 1: Using the RDP File
1.	Open the downloaded Remote Desktop File (e.g., myfirstec2machine.rdp).
2.	Click Connect when the prompt appears.
3.	Paste the password you copied earlier.
4.	Click Yes on the certificate warning to establish the connection.
Option 2: Manual Connection
1.	Open the "Remote Desktop Connection" application on your local machine.
2.	Enter the Public IP address of the remote machine.
3.	Click Connect.
4.	Enter the credentials and the password you copied earlier.
5.	Click Yes on any security prompts.
C. HOW TO CONNECT THROUGH PUTTY (SSH)
1.	Copy the Public IP address of your machine.
2.	Download and open PuTTY on your local machine.
3.	In the "Host Name (or IP address)" field, paste the copied IP address.
4.	In the left-hand category menu, navigate to: Connection > SSH > Auth > Credentials.
5.	Under "Private key file for authentication," click Browse.
6.	Select your Private Key file (usually .ppk format for PuTTY) and click Open.
7.	Click Open at the bottom of the PuTTY window.
8.	Click Accept on the security alert and log in (usually as 'ec2-user', 'admin', or 'ubuntu').
